0f778c52-e775-443a-b625-27e7ab94ba6b.07ad4c2c-3629-4d84-b4fb-490f63a32aa8.prompt=Virtual Machine\: 0f778c52-e775-443a-b625-27e7ab94ba6b.164c4463-376e-428d-933a-b1339faa620e.prompt=Password\: 0f778c52-e775-443a-b625-27e7ab94ba6b.21de4f83-0c2d-4411-bf82-b398fc9098ac.prompt=VMWare Host\: 0f778c52-e775-443a-b625-27e7ab94ba6b.29391ea8-4452-44d2-bdd2-0bf6370dc827.description=
Search for VMWare objects of type propsType and their properties (propsPathset) from a root object (if any) specified by propsRootObj and propsRootObj. Retrieve each object's properties one at a time from an initial search query ala SQL Query operation. Please see VMWare Integration Guide for more details.

Inputs\:
host - VMWare host hostname or IP
user - VMWare username
password - VMWare user's password
port - Port to connect on
protocol - Connection protocol (http or https)
closeSession - Close the internally kept VMWare Infrastructure API session at completion of operation?
propsType - VMWare properties type (Task, Datacenter, VirtualMachine, etc.) to filter on. Type of object results desired.
propsPathset - Property filter's pathset, comma-delimited (eg. name, info.name, runtime.host)
propsRootObjType - VMWare object type (eg. VirtualMachine, HostSystem, ComputeResource,ResourcePool,Alarm)
propsRootObj - VMWare object ID

Responses\:
success - The operation completed successfully.
failure - Something went wrong.
no more - there are no more results to retrieve.

Returns\:
hardDisk - boot disk space allocated for the VM.
ipaddess - IPAddress of the VM
macaddres - Mac Address of the VM.
0f778c52-e775-443a-b625-27e7ab94ba6b.2e789f07-b148-483e-9f9f-75bfb989f501.prompt=User Identifier 0f778c52-e775-443a-b625-27e7ab94ba6b.30be32a9-fd6c-4993-91d6-e6bd7cb7769e.prompt=VMWare User\: 0f778c52-e775-443a-b625-27e7ab94ba6b.5604425a-40d9-4530-812b-dbb8d19bae7d.prompt=Guest OS ID\: 0f778c52-e775-443a-b625-27e7ab94ba6b.56cdb55d-17b8-4495-8df0-6878f4c17a25.prompt=VMWare User\: 0f778c52-e775-443a-b625-27e7ab94ba6b.5dacc33c-1dbf-4523-8e2c-e984d8ae83a1.prompt=VMWare Host\: 0f778c52-e775-443a-b625-27e7ab94ba6b.62998c32-12b5-4035-8f77-2d07bf07baab.prompt=Password\: 0f778c52-e775-443a-b625-27e7ab94ba6b.64cccc96-aec0-4b97-b9e3-9c442993b29e.description=

Inputs\:

0f778c52-e775-443a-b625-27e7ab94ba6b.6f009953-dde7-43ee-83c5-e94125052ba3.prompt=Datastore\: 0f778c52-e775-443a-b625-27e7ab94ba6b.76c3a5f6-7c1d-4dfd-92aa-463e77053f7c.prompt=Virtual Machine name\: 0f778c52-e775-443a-b625-27e7ab94ba6b.774d512b-bf4e-4ed7-9018-52774cc4bb4e.prompt=Datacenter to create in\: 0f778c52-e775-443a-b625-27e7ab94ba6b.7a2777ff-5929-4cd5-b112-9f006cc5d50b.prompt=VMWare User\: 0f778c52-e775-443a-b625-27e7ab94ba6b.8c8a616d-daa4-437d-a31a-7a1318df0f50.description= Inputs\: host - vCenter DNS name/IP Address username - vCenter user password - vCenter user password port - vCenter port protocol - vCenter protocol hypervisorName - Hypervisor DNS name/IP Address dataStore - Datastore of the hypervior datacenterName - Datacenter name hostname - VM Server name FQDN - Fully Qualified Domain Name of the VM. templateReference - VM Template name osType - OS Type of the template CPUs - CPU Count to be assigned Memory - Memory Size to be assigned Results\: vmId - VM Identifies of the created VM ipAddress - IP Address of the created VM macAddress - MAC Address of the created VM 0f778c52-e775-443a-b625-27e7ab94ba6b.93d920f1-0285-465b-bac1-8eead25987f8.prompt=Target datacenter\: 0f778c52-e775-443a-b625-27e7ab94ba6b.a0b85c98-eae8-4bbe-bf21-afbf53a2d9ec.prompt=Virtual Machine\: 0f778c52-e775-443a-b625-27e7ab94ba6b.a3178587-4ffe-4875-9293-374686563dc7.prompt=VMWare Host\: 0f778c52-e775-443a-b625-27e7ab94ba6b.a4c5b024-69b1-428e-98b4-4d5947084cfb.prompt=VMWare Host\: 0f778c52-e775-443a-b625-27e7ab94ba6b.abdeb357-2836-4195-bd2c-573ff811e664.description=
 
Check to see if the value stored in a specified flow variable, denoted by key, is null.

Inputs\:
    keyName - The key to check, i.e. the name of the flow variable. 
    trimSpaces - If set on "true" then all the whitespaces will be removed from the value stored. 
Valid values\: true, false
Default value\: false

Returns\: 
    The value in the specified key, i.e. flow variable with all whitespaces removed.

Responses\:
    isNull - If the key is a null pointer, i.e. the flow variable doesn't have an assigned value.
    notNull - If some value is stored in the key, i.e the flow variable has a value assigned. 

Notes\: 
    1. If the "trimSpaces" input is set on "true" and the value from "keyName" contains only whitespaces then the response will be "isNull". 
    2. If the "trimSpaces" input is set on "false" and the value from "keyName" contains only whitespaces then the response will be "notNull". 
    3. If any other value than "true" or "false" is passed on "trimSpaces" input then the default value (false) will be used.
0f778c52-e775-443a-b625-27e7ab94ba6b.c9fc9e02-d94f-45b8-836a-056ec761ac85.prompt=Password\: 0f778c52-e775-443a-b625-27e7ab94ba6b.description=This flow is used to deploy VM from a template. If the ipAddress, dnsServer, subnetMask and gatewayIp property values are specified then it will create VM with given IP configuration otherwise it will create VM with dynamic IP. Inputs\: resourceLocation - The provider ID where the virtual machine needs to be deployed. diskPath - Path of the ISO image ipAddress - IP address of the virtual machine. ipType - IP Type specifies whether it is STATIC IP or not. dnsServer - DNS Server of the STATIC IP. subnetMask - Subnet Mask IP of the STATIC IP. gatewayIP - Gateway IP of the STATIC IP. memory - The size of the server's memory number_of_cpu - Number of cpus to be set on the VMs VirtualMachine - Virtual Machine is a software computer that, like a physical computer, runs on an operating system and applications datacenterName - Primary container of inventory objects such as hosts and virtual machines vmNamePrefix -Prefix of the provisioned VM name - Name of the VirtualMachine vmFolder - This represents root folder path for provisioned a VM vmResourcePool - VM ResourcePool delegate control over resources of a host (or a cluster) hostSystem - Host System for the deployed VM thinProvision - These virtual disks do not reserve space on the VMFS filesystem vCenterCustomizationTemplateName - Guest Customization Options used to include like computer name,network,Domain,Time Zone etc remoteConsolePassword - Remote Console Password is used to login the server for remote access vCenterRemoteConsolePort - Remote Console Port is used for remote access for the particular provisioned server datastore - Name of the Datastore under the selected for VM Subscription. networkName - Network name for the particular VM guestOSID - Value of Guest OS Id of deployed VM clusterName - This value represents name of the cluster where Host of the VM is located. version - Version of the particular deployed VM. netNicType - Value of Adapter Type. controllerType - This value represents different types of SCSI controller type including BusLogic Parallel, LSI Logic Parallel, LSI Logic SAS, and VMware Paravirtual SCSI Outputs\: FQDN - Fully Qualified Domain Name of the VM. Guest OS - Value of Guest OS details. Host Name - Hostname of the deployed server IP Address - IP address of the virtual machine. Power State - Power State of the VM. eg- OFF, ON Provider ID - The provider ID where the virtual machine needs to be deployed. Type of OS Image - Type of operating system installed, whether Windows, Linux etc VM Datacenter Name - Primary container of inventory objects such as hosts and virtual machines VM ID - ID of the VM. VM Name - Name of the VM. Responses\: success - The operation completed successfully. failure - Something went wrong. 0f778c52-e775-443a-b625-27e7ab94ba6b.e4e2d1de-0c06-414a-9d89-a365c6e8481c.prompt=Folder (inventory) path in datacenter\: 0f778c52-e775-443a-b625-27e7ab94ba6b.f850e23a-42e4-4228-a439-d9cf09504101.description=
This workflow will generate hostname based on subscription name and uuid. 20 charactes from subscription and 15 characters from uuid are appended to create unique id. For Windows  15 characters from uuid are parsed to create the hostname

Inputs\:

subscriptionId	- Subscription ID
uuid		- UUID of server component Id
userIdentifier	- User Identifier to pass to the wrapper flow to retrieve the child components


Returns
ObjectId 	- Returns hostname

Responses\:
success - Workflow completed successfully.
failure - Something went wrong.
